If you're okay with reading the textbook rather than relying on lectures, you'll be fine. This is by far the worst prof I have ever encountered. As others have said, in replacement of an actual lecture she uploads 15-25 minute videos of herself reading slides word for word. This prof does not care about you- she uploads herself reading the slides. Her exam is based on you writing close to 4 thousand words to answer 10 questions with NO mark breakdown. I wish I could rate her below 0. I don't know why I signed up to see her do a weekly reading comprehension during her prerecorded lectures. horrible prof who makes the content so dry and boring. Relies on videos to do her teaching and reads slides verbatim with info that comes from textbook. 1 midterm 1 final. Does not seem to want to help students at all, I find the way she teaches is very monotonous.

Posts lectures ahead of time for you to view at your own pace. Never had a synchronous lecture. Kept exam format from in-person class but left it open book. 2 tests; 40 & 50% and 2 quick assignments worth 5% each.

I have only had this prof once, but she was very kind and extremely accommodating to my particular situation. She is clearly a caring prof that delivers material in a very comprehendible way. The class was reading heavy but a good experience overall

Her lectures are dreadful. You watch pointless movies. Her slides have facts from the early 2000's Had her for Death and Dying and also Family. Just brutal. She skips so many slides, but every slide is on the midterm

Mary Theresa Howard does not follow her own syllabus. We are easily at least 2 classes behind, at all times. She speaks off topic after each and every slide. Amazing Prof!! I have had her 4 times and loved her each time. It's pretty easy to do well in class if you pay some attention to the videos and read the slides. She takes exam questions right from the slides and you'll do better on exams if you reference her films but she never asks about them on tests. If you do this you will probably do well

People find her courses hard because she has an unconventional marking scheme. 1) Don't skip a single class 2) Take notes on what *isn't* in her slides - her anecdotes, what she elaborates on 3) Note any videos shown (title and something specific from each video) 4) Mix with slide notes 5) Do bonus hw On tests, study 1-4 for A and submit 5 for A+

Incredibly interesting topic. Professor Howard is very knowledgeable, although perhaps some of her media was a little dated. 100% handwritten, point form short answer exams - I prefer multiple choice. Professor Howard is an amazing lecturer and actually so hilarious! She fills her lectures with anecdotes that enable you to better grasp the content of what she is teaching. As for comments about people finding her cold, I would disagree. People can be harsh on intelligent women...

She is honestly my one of my favourite profs at uO. If you hate multiple choice exams, take her class. Having her as a prof ruined a class I was excited for. Boring lectures, outdated films/content, she's rude.
